<TITLE> MPs to have security cards, swimming pool </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jun 21 (bdnews24.com)Speaker of the House Abdul Hamid has said the parliament complex will get a new security card system and a swimming pool. Hamid said MPs are already in the process of receiving a revised package of facilities which will include cars, parliament and constituency offices and increased salaries and bonuses. "The House must be turned into a centre of action. Everyone must work in unison to uphold the image of the House," Hamid told reporters Sunday at parliament. Out of a total 392 MPs, 92 have so far been allotted their offices at the old MP Hostel; they include 60 from the Awami League, 21 from BNP, 10 from JP and one from Jamaat-e-Islami. The Speaker also announced that an office assistant will be appointed to every MP. Hamid added that energy conservation measures would include the suspension of power to offices from 10pm to 9am. bdnews24
